ZCZC GE55
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 172300 UTC
ON SATURDAY EVENING A COMPLEX AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WILL
COVER MUCH OF THE UNITED KINGDOM WITH HIGH PRESSURE
COVERING THE NORWEGIAN SEA. THE COMPLEX LOW WILL MOV A
LITTLE FURTHER NEWARDS ON SUNDAY AND MONDAY WITH A SLACK
PRESSURE PATTERN DEVELOPING ACROSS MOST SERN AREAS OF
CULLERCOATS. A BROAD RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL EXTEND
SWARDS ACROSS MOST AREAS DURING THE COURSE OF TUESDAY.
WINDS WILL BE LIGHT AND VRB ACROSS THAMES DOVER AND
WIGHT ON SATURDAY EVENING. ACROSS REMAINING AREAS WINDS
WILL BE STRG SE AND THE STRGEST WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS S
UTSIRE FORTIES AND FISHER DURING SUNDAY MORNING. BY
SUNDAY AFTERNOON WINDS WILL BE LIGHT ACROSS ALL SERN
AREAS OF CULLERCOATS. ON MONDAY AND TUESDAY SE WINDS WILL
CONTINUE TO SLWY DECREASE ACROSS NERN AREAS AND BY
TUESDAY EVENING WINDS ACROSS THESE AREAS WILL BE LIGHT E
OR SE
